content: Works smoothly and quickly . Easy to use and very accurate @ where my current location is, Highly rec this app to any photographer that likes to use the Sun or Moon in their Shots.

It would be fantastic tool if you are landscape photographer,  I installed it and try to use it,  There is some missing functionalities, App works as long as you have data signal,  If App gives me a simple campus and points the moon and sun direction, it will be so helpful when I'm in the area with no signal,  If App gives me the very basic lunar calendar monthly table, it will be helpful when I want arrange some outing plan,  I appreciate App and whoever made it,  Completely, totally recommendable,
Works perfectly on both my devices.

Pure Awesomeness

This app is so much better than sundroid.. so many more options...  I would like to see reminders that link to alarms on my phone or to Google Calendars?? For instance, I used this app to predict where the sun would be in relation to a certain building in my hometown and discovered that it would be in the perfect spot on April 19th 2013.. I could set a reminder in my Google calendars, but it would be much easier if this app allowed me to set up an alert from the interface...(doesn't even have to be with Google Calendars)   Sundroid will allow me to set "alarms" for certain days etc in relation to the sun/moon rise/set/Twilight... etc etc... This capability would be perfect for your app..   Found this app when it was mentioned in March 2013 Outdoor Photographer Magazine... (pg 72)   JUST AWESOME stuff!! Highly recommended...  Samsung GS3
Can I rate it 10 stars?! Amazing app! Intuitive, fast and acts like it was actually developed by a human photographer! GET IT!

Perfect

Disappointing, especially given the personal recommendations from other photographers.   For photography use - Sun Surveyor.  It has better tools, offline ability, 3d compass, pre-saved locations, ability to easily share data & so much more! And a bonus - a lot cheaper.

Good app, but unfortunately it does not show sun/moon rise/set lines, when zoomed in. This happens on my Galaxy Nexus JB. Hope you correct it soon.  update: OK, your suggestion worked, turned "Settings/Dev/Force CPU Rendering off" and everything works now as expected.  So the app is absolutely indispensable, thank you :)

Works nicely on Nexus 7. Well presented and easy to understand. It would be nice to incorporate the weather forecast in a future version. Not sure why it needs to read phone status & identity though, so loses a star rating. Otherwise excellent.

I got a small gingerbread phone which it works on but boy you need tiny fingers. But on my Archos 80 G9 its much easier. BTW in case you didn't know once you have paid the Â£3ish. You can use it on all your Android devices . All I need now is a normal summer

Have used the PC desktop version for a while. Was ecstatic when I recently noticed an android version was released. I never schedule an outdoor photo shoot without checking the location on TPE first. Some occasional glitches, but I suspect google maps is the root of the problem.

For the keen photographer, amateur, or even pro, this app is very usefull for working out sunrise, sunsets at those locations you love to take photos at.  You already can easily find the time for sunrise and sunset times, this app goes further and allows you to know from where it will rise, and set.

I have been using this application since it came out using Adobe Air and was free to use.  I paid for the app, no regrets...  Quickly now sunset/sunrise times and the direction of the light so you can plan your shots ahead of time.  Check it out.
Almost perfect. Additionally to the requests of VimDinVT I'd like to suggest a way to exchange my locations and geodetic infos between my phone and pc. Thanks for this powerful tool!

This is a great app that does just about everything I want.  Would be nice to be able to change the map style to the terrain topo that Google offers.  What I would really like to see is an Augmented Reality option that could overlay the solar and lunar transit arcs over a live view from your phone's camera.  See satellite finder apps like Satellite Locator AR for an idea of what I'm talking about, they use it to check for satellite obstructions when setting up your dish.  That would be helpful in planning what day the sun would break though the gap in the trees, mountain, etc. at your present location.
I used the free desktop version to approximate my locations for many trips before I got a tablet. I'm glad I can help out a great programmer and photo enthusiast!
I actually use this program.  Great tool
The best tool!  Thanks ephemeris!

this is a great app highly  recommended

The most useful photo tool I have on my phone and tablet. Highly recommended.

This app is brilliant!

When I was going to ditch my iPhone, TPE the reason I couldn't. When I found that TPE was coming for Android I had no hesitation in jumping ship, the first app I bought  was TPE!  This app has helped me out so many times. I use desktop one to do the initial shoot planning then when I arrive the first thing I do "on site" is check the mobile TPE as it allows me to adjust my position "on site". If you shoot landscapes you need this now! No ifs or buts! Buy it now!
I've always loved the desktop version, and I'm very happy to have it on mobile now!
Have used the desktop version for a while, glad it's now on Android. Very useful and works well on 2.3 HTC desire s.
This really helps in planning architectural photography shoots.  Very useful and easy to use!

This app is almost as great as the desktop program. My only complaint, though it is a big one to me, is the lack of terrain view on the map. I only use terrain view on the desktop application as I live in an area surrounded by lower mountains that don't stand out on satellite or map view, but do perfectly in terrain view enabling easy use of the secondary marker. Please incorporate that into an update. That would make it absolutely perfect!
Brilliant. Dare I ask for the maps to align themselves with the compass as an option / alternative to the traditional "North up" view?

I've been using the desktop version for years. Its a critical tool for location research and planning. I'm now running it on my old T-Mobile MyTouch (Froyo) - handy. Also have it on my Viewsonic G-Tablet with gtabcomb custom ROM - gorgeous! Its fantastic to have TPE on location and on the road.
YES! Been waiting for this for what seems like forever! Can't wait to use this on my first shoot.

Now available for Android, and working flawlessly. As intuitive as the desktop version, but now it's out in Android user's pockets, in the field, where it really shines.  While a wonderful "planning" tool on the desktop, this mobile version adds "real time" usefulness to it.  Useful even without a network connection, since calculations are local.  Long available for iPhone, now on the most popular mobile OS.  Outstanding!
I have this installed on my Droid X and Galaxy Tab 10.1. Both work great. I have been using this on my PC for years.
Long-time user of TPE for desktop. I have tried all the other similar apps in the Android market, but none are as good as TPE.  Thanks Stephen Trainor
